processGroups.comments: Exports annotations and records that are used by CogStack-Cohort.

labels.label: Step II: execute this only once. Currently this works with static file names that you have to declare in the "arguments" property."
Optional, change the minimum amount of files to be merged. Change the schedule from 10 min to something else if you have less files to pull
Optional, change the minimum amount of files to be merged.

You MUST set/change the following parameters:
patient_id_field_name="patient" patient_ethnicity_field_name="ethnicity" patient_gender_field_name="gender" patient_birth_date_field_name="birthdate" patient_death_date_field_name="deathdate"
The source of the document id, always use the "meta.docid" or "meta.document_id_field" that you declared when annotating documents, the prefix will be cutoff, it must be the same field name as in the original patient record docs
annotation_document_id_field_name="meta.docid"
IMPORTANT: you may also need to set the date and time format. the fields that have dates in them should be the same format. Set via the "date_time_format" argument (Default: %Y-%m-%d).
Place these parameters in the "Command arguments" property, delimited by ";".
Send only 1 flowfile / sec to guarantee timestamp uniqueness
change the index name here to the annotations one
Modify the Query parameter to include/exclude fields, you should exclude the "text" field as you won't be using it here. For the samples DB, the text field is "document". Also the change index name.

Modify the patterns for the annotations and the patient data files, these are matched by simple string search:
input_annotations_records_file_name_pattern=medical_reports_anns_ input_patient_record_file_name_pattern=medical_reports_text_
Modify where the output of the files should be and where should the above be picked from:
output_folder_path="/opt/data/cogstack-cohort/" input_folder_path="/opt/data/cogstack-cohort/"
Change the "*.docid" to whatever field represents it. This processor does NOT support ExpressionLanguage
Again, change the bin size and scheduling if you have less files
